    - [Nair et al 1984](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6531443)
    - [Brown et al 1985](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/4014502) & [Frazer et al 1986](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3462336/) (2 studies; in both, depressed had reduced melatonin secretion. Frazer's abstract notes that "These results are similar to those found recently by several other groups of investigators." Indeed.)
    - [Kennedy et al 1989](http://archpsyc.ama-assn.org/cgi/content/abstract/46/1/73) (controls vs eating disorder victims; only eating disorder plus depression correlated with lower melatonin)
    - [Shafii et al 1996](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8911224) ("Post hoc analysis showed a significantly higher melatonin profile in depressed subjects without psychosis (n = 15) than in depressed subjects with psychosis (n = 7) or in the controls.")
